a in Lycia, about whom virtually nothing factual is known, although a vast body of legend grew up around him, and he became the patron saint of Greece and of Russia, as well as of children, sailors, merchants, and pawnbrokers. His feast day is  6 December , and among the many roles which legend has assigned to him is that of bringer of Christmas presents, in the guise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Nicolaus de Podebusk was born in 1218, in Of, Trabzon, Türkiye, his father, Stoislaw von Rügen I, was 78 and his mother, Irmingard Knudsdatter af Danmark, was 71. He married Mrs. Nicolau von Podebusk about 1219. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. He died on 31 October 1315, in Vilmnitz, Rügen, Pomerania, Prussia, Germany, at the age of 97."},"et":{"1218–31 OCT 1315":"1218–31. oktoober 1315","1187–1237":"1187–1237","1218–1315":"1218–1315","1190–Female":"1190–Surnud","1221–1253":"1221–1253","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","1140–1193":"1140–1193","1147–Female":"1147–Surnud","1190":"1190","1253":"1253","1187":"1187","1140":"1140","1193":"1193","ABT 1219":"umbes 1219","1315":"1315","1237":"1237","31 OCT 1315":"31. oktoober 1315","1225":"1225","1147":"1147","1221":"1221","ABT. 1225":"umbes 1225","1218":"1218","Rügen, Rügen, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Saksa":"Rügen, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Saksamaa","Putbus, Putbus, Rügen, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Saksa":"Putbus, Rügen, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Saksamaa","of Borantehangen and Putbus, Rugen, Pomerania":"Putbus, Rügen, Pommern, Freistaat Preußen, Saksamaa","Of, Vilmnitz, Pommern, Prussia":"Vilmnitz, Rügen, Pommern, Freistaat Preußen, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1218–31 OCT 1315":"1218–31. lokakuuta 1315","1187–1237":"1187–1237","1218–1315":"1218–1315","1190–Female":"1190–Kuollut","1221–1253":"1221–1253","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","1140–1193":"1140–1193","1147–Female":"1147–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1253":"1253","1187":"1187","1140":"1140","1193":"1193","ABT 12